cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DB, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new data structure for representing temporal graphs. 
- cs.SI (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the Compressed Suffix Array (CSA) is a well-known data structure in the area of text indexing. 
- cs.SD (Software Development and Programming) is a possible category as the paper involves implementing and testing the new data structure. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as the paper deals with representing and querying large amounts of data. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on social or ethical issues related to computing.
